  <data name="label2.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>An In-Game Diary. 
This won’t affect the gameplay or 
does it required to accomplish something. 
Feel free to write your thoughts, 
negative or positive.

The game dev won’t have any access to your 
entries or be able to help with your situation.
If at any time you believe you require urgent 
medical attention, do not hesitate to reach 
out for professional help or call your local 
emergency hotlines.

“Finding Nimo” hopes to reach its players 
and offer a small sense of comfort. 


Remember, someone may care for you. 
And if it feels like no one does, 
please try to reach out to someone
who can support you.</value>
